&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a Community Moderator. This is a full-time position based in Brooklyn, NY reporting into the Airtime Marketing team.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In this role, you’ll wear many hats. Flexibility and a willingness to quickly move between projects and tasks are key. We’re looking for a people person who is all about helping others. You must also be comfortable with moderating content that may be sexual, violent, or disturbing in nature.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Primary responsibilities:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Support -- replying to our users’ customer service inquiries and filing bug reports.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Content moderation -- investigating and actioning reports of inappropriate content.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;You’ll also have the opportunity to follow your interests with project work in this role, in addition to the two ticket-focused tasks above. You may be working with the User Insights team to create surveys, schedule interviews, and craft other outgoing communications for users. You may work to create new spaces on our app around your own personal interests, whether that’s knitting, watching Empire, skydiving, sandwiches, Drake, otters, anything! Sky’s the limit.&lt;/li&gt;
